%e A210250 48 is in the sequence because, for (a,b,c,d) = (6,6,8,8),
%e A210250 s = (6+6+8+8)/2 = 14;
%e A210250 A = sqrt((14-6)(14-6)(14-8)(14-8)) = 48;
%e A210250 R = sqrt((6*6+8*8)(6*8+6*8)(6*8+6*8))/(4*48) = 960/192 = 5.
